### Flex Wrap

**flex-wrap** controls whether flex items wrap to a new line.

---

### Values

| Value | Effect |
|-------|--------|
| `nowrap` | All items on one line (default) |
| `wrap` | Items wrap to new lines |
| `wrap-reverse` | Items wrap in reverse direction |

---

### Nowrap (Default)

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: nowrap;
}
```

Items stay on one line. Items may shrink or overflow.

---

### Wrap

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
```

Items wrap to next line when they don't fit.

---

### Wrap-Reverse

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap-reverse;
}
```

Items wrap upwards (reverse order).

---

### With Flex Basis

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 20px;
}

.item {
  flex: 0 0 200px; /* Fixed width items that wrap */
}
```

Items with `flex-basis: 200px` wrap when container is narrow.

---

### Align Content (with Wrap)

When items wrap into multiple lines, `align-content` controls line spacing:

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  align-content: center;     /* Lines centered */
  align-content: space-between; /* Even space between lines */
  align-content: stretch;    /* Lines stretch (default) */
}
```

---

### Responsive Cards Example

```css
.card-grid {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 20px;
}

.card {
  flex: 1 1 300px; /* Grow, shrink, basis 300px */
  /* 3 cards on desktop, 2 on tablet, 1 on mobile */
}
```

---

> **Best Practice:** Always use `flex-wrap: wrap` for responsive layouts. Use `gap` for spacing instead of margins.
